Text.Value: You'll, uh... remind me?
So, Vistra. You reckon we'd still be better Fists than the current cohort?
Come off it, Vistra. You've been doing this same rant for years.
You've known me long enough, Vistra. When haven't I?
Peace of piss, mate. Easy. Yes.
Those cultists are lucky they were on the other side of the park. Lucky.
Bollocks. These days we'd sooner throw our backs than a proper punch.
We knew how to watch each other's backs.
Thanks to the bloody Iron Crisis we barely had any metal back then.
Not seen action like that in a while.
Same here. My knees are buggered already, never mind running after cultists.
Lost a lot of good men that day.
Great. So let's get you out of that chair and into your chain mail, then? Show the young lot how it's done?
Limp gloves.
You make a good point, Eldaernth.
Well, I, for one, count my lucky stars it happened elsewhere.
It's a young man's game. Right, Vistra?
'Spose.
You're right, you're right. We Fists had to proper fight back then.
Back when the Fists were real Fists. Not bloody...
You're remembering the past pretty fondly, Vistra. Bit too fondly.
You telling me you'd have refused the Steel Watch's help on Returning Day a decade ago?
Look, all I'm saying is they've got it easier these days.
Uh... Well...
Yeah, we didn't have these big metal bastards running the streets back in my day.
Yeah, to be honest? Thought of holding a pike makes my back ache.
Yeah, the first lot of young folk you said it about are old folk now!
Piss off, the lot of youse.
'Absolute' this... 'end of the word' that... These young folk've no idea how good they've got it.
Big horrible beast? Slaughtered Duke Adrian? We could do bugger all about it?
Helm give me strength.
You'd have taken them, would you, Vistra?
What d'you mean?
We could've used the Steel Watch back in the day. But that's because we fought actual threats.
My armour's not fit for years.
Reckon so.

Synopsis: Some retired Flaming Fist in the Lower City Park sit around complaining about the youth of today and revisiting former glories. All are elves and dwarves, so they can remember the events of BG1 if we want to reference that
